Anyone who incites Kenyans along the hustler versus dynasties split could be imprisoned for five years or pay a fine of Sh5 million.The law also gives the National Cohesion and Integration Commission additional powers to investigate incitement on the basis of ethnicity, racial or social status and recommend necessary disciplinary action Deputy President William Ruto’s ‘hustlers versus dynasties’ campaign slogan could soon land him and his political allies in jail, in addition to being banned from holding public office, if a proposed Bill is passed into law.   

Lawmakers have drafted a Bill that imposes severe fines, jail time and makes it a basis for removal from office any leader who propagates ‘class divisions’ in the country. 



